07/06/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- An additional 10,000-member police force will arrive in Istanbul to reinforce security during the 28 June-29 June NATO summit, Interior Minister Abdulkadir Aksu said Sunday (6 June). 
The security department, gendarme forces command, and the coast guard command will jointly provide summit security.
Also Sunday, Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul arrived in Egypt for meetings with local officials as part of preparations for the Organisation of the Islamic Conference meeting that will be held in Istanbul next week.
Meanwhile, Turkish Labour and Social Security Minister Murat Basesgioglu is in Geneva, Switzerland, attending the 92nd International Conference of the International Labour Organisation. 
Labour ministers from 177 member states were invited. 
(Anadolu Agency, NTV, TRT 2 - 06/06/04)
